# UPDATE in db

### Update Operators

- `$addFields`
- `$set`
- `$project`
- `$unset`
- `$replaceRoot`
- `$replaceWith`

<br>

### updateOne()

Updates at most a single document that match a specified filter even through multiple documents may match the specified filter.

```bash
db.collection.updateOne(<filter>, <update>, <alter>)
```

`$set` updates the existing field, if the field doesn't exists in the document then it creates the same.

```bash
db.student.updateOne( {name: "Raunak"}, {$set: {age: 19}} )
```

<br>

### updateMany()

Updates all documents that match a specified filter.

```bash
db.collection.updateMany(<filter>, <update>, <alter>)
```

```bash
db.student.updateMany( {city: "Delhi"}, {$set: {city: "New Delhi"}} )
```

<br>

### replaceOne()

Replace at most a single document that match a specified filter event through multiple documents may match the specified filter.

```bash
db.collection.replaceOne(<filter>, <update>, <alter>)
```
```bash
db.student.replaceOne( {name: "Suhani"}, {name: "Suhani" ,city: "New Delhi", age: 20, marks: 100} )
```

<br>

[Click here](https://www.mongodb.com/docs/manual/tutorial/update-documents-with-aggregation-pipeline/) for more info.